wiki.content: "It Hurts Me Too" is a song written by Tampa Red and made famous by Elmore James in 1957. It became one of James' most famous songs. As a blues standard, it has been covered by many artists: User-contributed text is available under the Creative Commons By-SA License and may also be available under the GNU FDL.
wiki.summary: "It Hurts Me Too" is a song written by Tampa Red and made famous by Elmore James in 1957. It became one of James' most famous songs. As a blues standard, it has been covered by many artists:

track.name: It Hurts Me Too
comments: First heard this when I was sixteen and bought it on an imported US vinyl single, still brilliant!
Oh my.......my...my....the guitar and the voice.....Salud!
he still is ELMORE JAMES!  forever honest.
first heard this by Keb Mo..nice to hear the original
They broke the mold when EJ was killed
It hurts a lot less, though, when Elmore is singing and strumming. (-:
A little out of key...but who gives a flyin' burrioto. It's ELMORE for gawds sake ! Love it!
Great stuff from The Elmore. Sweet guitar...oh yea!
first class, blues is the truth!!!!
